         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he gave to the mendicants alms with his own hand ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... den bettelnden Wesen (gab er) mit eigener Hand {G}aben. Speisen wurden gekocht, [und] er gab den Vögeln [wtl. das hüpfende Tier] [und] Wassertieren Gaben.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... to the begging beings (he gave) gifts with [his] own hand. Food was cooked, [and] he gave gifts to the birds [lit. the hopping animal] [and] to the water animals.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>226</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2 #a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wenn er in den Palast [wtl. das königliche Haus] ging, sah er [seinen] Vater, den König, bald nach dem Gesetz, bald nicht nach dem Gesetz Befehl gebend.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">When[ever] he went into the palace [lit. the royal house], he saw [his] father, the king, giving orders, sometimes according to the law, sometimes not according to the law.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>189</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3 #a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Er bat um Erlaubnis, aus dem Hause zu gehen [d.h. Mönch zu werden], [aber] er erhielt nicht die Erlaubnis, aus dem Hause zu gehen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">He asked for permission to go out of the house, [but] he did not get permission to go out of the house.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>197, 422</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #b1 #b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Da er den starken Entschluss, aus dem Hause zu gehen, gefasst hatte, aß er am ersten Tage [und] auch am zweiten Tage keine Speise. [Auch] am dritten Tage [und] am vierten Tage (aß er) nicht, [und] am fünften Tage aß er keine Speise. Vielmehr gab er sich selbst hin zu verhungern.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Since he had made the strong decision to go out of the house, on the first [and] on the second day he ate no food. On the third day [and] on the fourth day, [also,] (he) did not (eat), [and] on the fifth day, he ate no food [either]. Rather, he gave himself up to starvation.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>317-8</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... on the first and on the second day he did not eat any food; [also] on the third [and] on the fourth day (he did) not (eat), [and] on the fifth day he did not eat any food ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Als darauf [sein] Vater Mahendradeva ... den Prinzen als einen, der sechs Tage ohne Speise geblieben war, erkannt hatte, gab er ihm [von sich aus] die Erlaubnis, aus dem Hause zu gehen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">When thereupon [his] father Mahendradeva ... had recognized the prince as one who had remained without food for six days, he [, of his own accord,] gave him permission to go out of the house.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>491</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
